<div id="main">
	<h2 class="imgrep advertise">Why Advertise with phpBB.com?</h2>
	<ul>
		<li>phpBB.com has a thriving community of over 250,000 registered users.</li>
		<li>phpBB.com gets over 10 million visits per month.</li>
		<li>phpBB.com receives over 40,000 visitors daily with over 8000 of those people downloading our software.</li>
		<li>phpBB.com has a very targeted audience of males mainly between 16 and 45 who are interested in the Internet and web site/hosting/development related issues.</li>
	</ul>
	
	<div class="column1" style="margin-bottom: 1.5em;">
		<h3 id="banners">Banner based advertising</h3>
		<p>With the launch of this new website, we are solely running a 728px &times; 90px leaderboard that is shown on the footer of every page of phpBB.com and is available under <abbr title="cost per mille">CPM</abbr> or <abbr title="price per click">PPC</abbr> based pricing. Campaigns are set up with a default weighting of 20, though by request can be changed to a maximum of 100 (5 times <strong>more</strong> likely for your advert to be show) to as low as 1 (20 times <strong>less</strong> likely for your advert to be show, useful for conserving impressions/clicks for those on a smaller budget).</p>
		
		<h4>Site zones*</h4>
		<p>In the near future, we intend to allow your advert to target specific sections of phpBB.com so that your advert is shown only on the home page, downloads pages, forum pages, search result pages or remaining website content pages.</p>
		
		<h4>Pricing*:</h4>
		<ul>
			<li>$2.00 <abbr title="cost per mille">CPM</abbr></li>
			<li>$0.25 <abbr title="price per click">PPC</abbr></li>
			<li>The minimum purchase is $50</li>
		</ul>
		<h4>Discounting:</h4>
		<ul>
			<li>For purchases of over $500 and below $5000, you gain an extra <strong>5%</strong> impressions (<abbr title="cost per mille">CPM</abbr> based) or clicks (<abbr title="price per click">PPC</abbr> based)</li>
			<li>For purchases of $5000 and over, you gain an extra <strong>10%</strong> impressions (<abbr title="cost per mille">CPM</abbr> based) or clicks (<abbr title="price per click">PPC</abbr> based)</li>
		</ul>
		<p><em>* Site zones and final <abbr title="cost per mille">CPM</abbr>/<abbr title="price per click">PPC</abbr> rates will be settled by <abbr title="2nd quarter">Q2</abbr> 2007.</em></p>
	</div>
	
	<div class="column2" style="margin-bottom: 1.5em;">
		<h3 id="textlinks">Text-link based advertising</h3>
		<p>With phpBB.com&rsquo;s high Google Pagerank and Alexa Traffic Ranking, text-link based advertising is one of the best ways to reach our extremely broad audience. The two main sections are our &ldquo;Sponsors&rdquo; block on the home page and footer links which run site wide, on every single page. Examples of what your text-link would look like are shown in the &ldquo;Sample text-link options&rdquo; panel.</p>
		
		<h4 id="standardlink">Standard links</h4>
		<p>Just a straight-forward link with no frills.</p>
		
		<h4 id="boldedlink">Bolded links</h4>
		<p>Add some visual emphasis to your link with this option.</p>
		
		<h4 id="faviconlink">Favicon branded links</h4>
		<p>Brand your site with a favicon? Why not brand your text-link in the same way?</p>
		
		<h4 id="boldiconlink">Bold &amp; Favicon branded links</h4>
		<p>Have both enhancements for a discounted rate!</p>
		
		<h4 id="linksentence">Link sentence</h4>
		<p>It is now possible to obtain some premium space by the way of getting the top 3 slots of our &ldquo;Sponsors&rdquo; and run a full sentence of no more than 35 words containing up to 3 unique links.</p>
		<h4>Pricing:</h4>
		
		<ul>
			<li>The pricing for text-links is significantly higher than pricing on our banner based advertising, so please <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20070701232739/mailto:%69%6E%76%6F%69%63%69%6E%67%40%70%68%70%62%62%2E%63%6F%6D">contact us</a> for pricing information about the various options.</li>
		</ul>
	</div>
	
	<hr/>
	
	<div class="mini-panel" style="float: right; margin: 15px 0 0 1em; width: 240px; clear: right;">
		<div class="inner"><span class="corners-top"><span></span></span>
		<h3>Ready to buy?</h3>
		<p>
			If you're ready to order advertising on phpBB.com please <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20070701232739/mailto:%69%6E%76%6F%69%63%69%6E%67%40%70%68%70%62%62%2E%63%6F%6D">email us</a> with the following details:
		</p>
		<ul>
			<li>A copy of your banner image or proposed link text along with enhancements options if appropiate</li>
			<li>Where you wish your banner or text ad to link to</li>
			<li>For banners, the number of impressions or clicks for your campaign, plus any adjustment in weighting</li>
		</ul>
		<p>
			Once we recieve this information we will review your request and if approved we will get back 
			to you within 3 working days with payment details and answers to any questions you may have.
		</p>
		<span class="corners-bottom"><span></span></span></div>
	</div>
	
	<h3 id="terms">Terms &amp; Conditions</h3>
	
	<h4 style="margin-top: 0;">Payment</h4>
	<ul>
		<li>Payment for any advertising campaign on phpBB.com must be received in full prior to the start of any campaign.</li> 
		<li>All prices are quoted in US Dollars and payment must be made in US Dollars.</li>
	</ul>
	
	<h4>Payment Options</h4>
	<ul>
		<li>Payments up to $2,000 can be made via Paypal, Business Cheque, Money Order, or Certified Cheque</li>
		<li>Payments up to $10,000 can be made by Business Cheque, Money Order, Certified Cheque or Wire Transfer</li>
		<li>Payments over $10,000 can be made by Wire Transfer, Money Order, or Certified Cheque.</li>
		<li>Personal Cheques are <strong>not</strong> accepted!</li>
	</ul>
	
	<h4>Cancellation</h4>
	<ul>
		<li>You may cancel your advertising with phpBB.com at any time.</li> 
		<li>For banners, the baseline $50 will not be refunded with the remainder of the campaign worth impressions or clicks reimbursed at a 80% rate.</li>
		<li>For text-links, partial months will not be refunded. Full remaining months will be refunded if more than one month has been purchased up front.</li>
	</ul>
	
	<h4>Content</h4>
	<ul>
		<li>Advertisements on phpBB.com will not be accepted if they contain:
			<ul>
				<li>Links to pornographic material</li>
				<li>Links to illegal material or actions (e.g.: warez sites)</li>
				<li>Links to sites that contain material not suitable for younger viewers (e.g.: Adult humor sites)</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
		<li>Any advertisements will be screened by the phpBB.com staff and we reserve the right to 
			reject any advertisement we find unacceptable to our audience.</li>
	</ul>
</div>

